			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Clay is a type of fine-grained natural soil material containing clay minerals such as hydrous aluminium phyllosilicates. Clays develop plasticity when wet but can be hardened through firing. Most pure clay minerals are white or light-coloured, but natural clays show a variety of colours. Clay materials are plastic when wet and coherent when dry. Clay minerals are a group of hydrous aluminosilicates that are formed from the weathering and alteration of silicate minerals.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">黏土是一种含有如水合铝酸盐等黏土矿物的细粒自然土壤材料。黏土在湿润时会变得塑性，但可以通过烧制来硬化。大多数纯黏土矿物是白色或浅色的，但自然黏土显示出各种颜色。黏土材料在湿润时是塑性的，干燥时是连贯的。黏土矿物是一组由硅酸盐矿物的风化和改变形成的含水铝硅酸盐。</common:generalComment>
			<sumFormula>Al 2 Si 2 O 5 ( OH) 4</sumFormula>
